{"id":"1505.05982","submitter":"Nicolas Rougerie","authors":"Douglas Lundholm (KTH), Nicolas Rougerie (LPMMC)","title":"The Average Field Approximation for Almost Bosonix Extended Anyons","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math-ph cond-mat.quant-gas math.AP math.MP math.SP","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Anyons are 2D or 1D quantum particles with intermediate statistics,\ninterpolating between bosons and fermions. We study the ground state of a large\nnumber N of 2D anyons, in a scaling limit where the statistics parameter is\nproportional to the inverse of N. This means that the statistics is seen as a\n\"perturbation from the bosonic end.\" We model this situation in the magnetic\ngauge picture by bosons interacting through long-range magnetic potentials. We\nassume that these effective statistical gauge potentials are generated by\nmagnetic charges carried by each particle, smeared over discs of radius R\n(extended anyons). Our method allows to take R to 0 not too fast at the same\ntime as N to infinity. In this limit we rigorously justify the so-called\n\"average field approximation\": the particles behave like independent,\nidentically distributed bosons interacting via a self-consistent magnetic\nfield.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 22 May 2015 08:24:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 11 Jun 2015 18:10:46 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 17 Sep 2015 12:50:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-09-18"}
